The other day we (me, Andrew Wang, and Sighduck) launched !SPLAT a commentary on the defaced Van Gogh by climate activists. 

We allow anyone to turn this NFT of a soup can, designed by Creature World's Danny Cole into a splatted version of any NFT (see next cast) https://i.imgur.com/ZveRcny.png

We built and shipped it in 4 days. 

It crazily sold out in 3 minutes, which blew our minds in this market (0.05 ETH, 1k supply)

How it works in the next cast https://i.imgur.com/34GnL5O.png

When you run the `splat` function in the contract, the contract emits an event, which our server listens to -> then it grabs the NFT metadata and the image, layers on a frame with a splat -> takes a composite screenshot -> uploads it -> changes the metadata and force updates the token on OpenSea

People have splatted Beeple, Fidenzas, Ringers, Punks, Squiggles, and more.

Splatting seems to be more of an honor than anything else right now, focused on some of the best of the best of NFTs (and that ON1 that Logan Paul paid $$$$ for lol)
